events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 27 points and the Golden State Warriors withstood a late surge by the Houston Rockets for a 105-98 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 27 points to lead the Warriors to a 105-98 win over the Rockets

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 37 of his 43 points after halftime — including 11 points in overtime — and the New Orleans Pelicans snapped a 10-game losing streak with a 140-133 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum scores 43 points to lift Pelicans over the Kings 140-133 in overtime

headlines.description: — Dante Exum scored a season-high 27 points, one short of his career high, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Miami Heat 118-113 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dante Exum scores 27 points to lead undermanned, undersized Mavericks past Heat, 118-113

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Naz Reid had 27 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists for the short-handed Minnesota Timberwolves in a 116-101 victory over Oklahoma...
headlines.shortLinkText: Naz Reid's 27 points help lead short-handed Timberwolves past West-leading Thunder 116-101

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored a season-high 41 points and James Harden added 32 to lift the Los Angeles Clippers to a 120-116 overtime victory over the Utah Jazz on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell scores 41 points, Harden has 32 to rally Clippers to 120-116 OT victory over Jazz
